function prefixScoreSum(words) {
    const result = new Array(words.length).fill(0);
    const prefixCount = {};

    for (const word of words) {
        let prefix = "";
        for (const c of word) {
            prefix += c;
            prefixCount[prefix] = (prefixCount[prefix] || 0) + 1;
        }
    }

    for (let i = 0; i < words.length; i++) {
        let prefix = "";
        for (const c of words[i]) {
            prefix += c;
            result[i] += prefixCount[prefix];
        }
    }

    return result;
}
```

    The algorithm works as follows:
1. For each word in `words`, count the number of occurrences of each of its prefixes using a dictionary/hashmap.
2. For each word in `words`, iterate through its prefixes and sum up the counts calculated in the previous step. Store the result for each word in the `result` list/array.

The algorithm's time complexity is O(n * max_len(words)), where n is the number of words and max_len(words) is the length of the longest word. The space complexity is also O(n * max_len(words)).

